## Gemini-Specific Features

### Large Context Window (2M tokens!)

Gemini can handle comprehensive context:

```bash
# Use detailed mode for full project view
idlergear context --mode detailed  # ~7,000 tokens - no problem!

# Can even use full mode if needed
idlergear context --mode full  # ~17,000+ tokens
```

### Multimodal Integration

Gemini can analyze images! Use this for architecture diagrams:

```bash
# Add architecture diagram as reference
idlergear reference add "System Architecture" --file docs/architecture.png

# Then ask Gemini: "Analyze the system architecture"
# Gemini will see and understand the diagram!
```

### Code Understanding

Gemini excels at cross-file reasoning - great for:
- Understanding how modules interact
- Analyzing complex architectures
- Finding patterns across files

## Context Modes

Since Gemini has a large window, prefer detailed/full modes:

- `--mode minimal`: ~750 tokens (use for quick checks)
- `--mode standard`: ~2,500 tokens (general work)
- `--mode detailed`: ~7,000 tokens (**recommended for Gemini!**)
- `--mode full`: ~17,000+ tokens (comprehensive analysis)

